    "plan_content": "## Plan: Add `ollama rename` to Ollama\n\nHere's my full implementation plan after reading all relevant source files. **4 files to modify**, zero new files needed.\n\n---\n\n### Architecture Overview\n\nOllama models are stored as:\n- **Manifests** (tiny JSON files): `$OLLAMA_MODELS/manifests/{host}/{namespace}/{model}/{tag}`\n- **Blobs** (actual weights, shared by digest): `$OLLAMA_MODELS/blobs/sha256-{hash}`\n\nA \"rename\" is simply: copy the manifest file to the new path, then delete the old one. Since blobs are shared by SHA256 digest, `RemoveLayers()` will see the new dst manifest still references all those digests and will skip deleting them — no data is lost.\n\n---\n\n### Step 1 — `api/types.go` (after line 765, after `CopyRequest`)\nAdd `RenameRequest` struct:\n```go\ntype RenameRequest struct {\n    Source      string `json:\"source\"`\n    Destination string `json:\"destination\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Step 2 — `api/client.go` (after line 387, after `Copy`)\nAdd `Rename` client method calling `POST /api/rename`.\n\n### Step 3 — `server/routes.go`\n- **Register route** after line 1698: `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)`\n- **Add `RenameHandler`** after `CopyHandler` (line 1483) with this logic:\n  1. Bind JSON → 400 on error\n  2. `model.ParseName` + `IsValid()` for both src/dst → 400 if invalid\n  3. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` → **404** if `os.IsNotExist`\n  4. `manifest.PathForName(dst)` + `os.Stat` → **409** if destination already exists\n  5. `CopyModel(src, dst)` → copies manifest JSON (blobs untouched)\n  6. `srcManifest.Remove()` → removes old manifest + prunes empty dirs\n  7. `srcManifest.RemoveLayers()` → skips all blobs (dst manifest protects them via `inUse` set)\n\n### Step 4 — `cmd/cmd.go`\n- Add `RenameHandler` func (after `CopyHandler`, line 1350): calls `client.Rename`, prints `\"renamed 'X' to 'Y'\"`\n- Add `renameCmd` cobra command (after `copyCmd`, line 2263): `Use: \"rename SOURCE DESTINATION\"`, `Args: cobra.ExactArgs(2)`, `PreRunE: checkServerHeartbeat`\n- Add `renameCmd` to both the env-docs loop (~line 2298) and `rootCmd.AddCommand` (~line 2345)",
